Matthew 21-30 <J>And he went to the other son and said the same. And he answered, ‘I go, sir,’ but did not go.</J>
Matthew 21-31 <J>Which of the two did the will of his father?”</J> They said, “The first.” Jesus said to them, <J>“Truly, I say to you, <f>ⓦ</f>the tax collectors and <f>ⓧ</f>the prostitutes go into <f>ⓨ</f>the kingdom of God before you.</J>
